## Chat Widget (public/chat-widget.js)

Embeddable via single script tag:
```html
<script src="https://your-backend-url/chat-widget.js"></script>
```

Self-contained IIFE. No dependencies. Auto-detects API base URL from its own script src attribute.
Floating chat bubble (60x60px, brand colour, bottom-right corner). Opens 380x520px chat window above bubble.
Dark theme matching admin dashboard.
Session persistence via localStorage (UUID per visitor, survives page reloads).
Rate limited server-side: 30 messages per 10 minutes per IP.
Lead capture feedback: success message displayed when chatbot captures a lead.
Form pre-fill: when chatbot tool returns formData, widget redirects to quote form with pre-filled fields.

---

## Quote Submission Flow (the core pipeline)

1. Customer submits form (Aura frontend or chat widget)
2. POST /api/quote validates required fields (name, email, phone, address, postcode)
3. Extracts services array from form data
4. Inserts to quotes table with status='new'
5. findOrCreateCustomer() auto-links/creates customer profile
6. syncQuoteToSheets() sends to Google Sheets (non-blocking)
7. queueEstimation() triggers async estimation (setTimeout 1s)
8. sendConfirmationEmail() sends immediate confirmation
9. sendConfirmationWhatsApp() sends WhatsApp confirmation
10. Returns success JSON to frontend
11. (Async) Estimation job runs: calculates estimate + lead score
12. (Async) Updates quotes table with results
13. (Async) Sends estimate email with accept button
14. (Async) Sends estimate WhatsApp with accept link
15. (Async) If hot lead: alerts admin via email + WhatsApp
16. (Async) Sets next_follow_up_at to 3 days from now
17. (Scheduled) Follow-up scheduler checks hourly, sends step 1 email at day 3, step 2 at day 7

---

## Key Patterns and Conventions

1. All route files export setSupabaseClient(client) — called from index.js on startup
2. Admin auth: middleware/auth.js checks Authorization: Bearer {ADMIN_TOKEN} header
3. Business details: BUSINESS_* env vars with empty string fallbacks
4. JSON body parsing: 15MB limit (for base64 receipt/attachment uploads)
5. CORS: Allow all origins (*), methods GET/POST/PATCH/DELETE/OPTIONS
6. Static files served from /public directory
7. Pricing config: DB settings table takes priority, config/pricing.js is fallback, 5-min cache
8. Estimation runs async (setTimeout 1s after quote insert) — customer gets instant response
9. Google Sheets sync is fire-and-forget (errors logged, not thrown)
10. All monetary values use NUMERIC(10,2) in database
11. UK-specific: British English, GBP currency, HMRC tax categories, April 6 tax year start, 0.45/mile rate
12. Receipt scanning uses Claude Sonnet (claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929) for vision OCR accuracy
13. Chatbot uses Claude Haiku (claude-haiku-4-5-20251001) for speed and cost
14. Receipt scanner returns items array for per-category splitting (mixed receipts)
15. Bulk receipt upload: sequential processing (avoids API rate limits), review queue before save
16. Quote acceptance: /accept-estimate/:id renders public HTML page, POST /confirm-acceptance/:id processes it
17. Invoice public view: /invoice/:token renders printable HTML with business details + print button
18. Team schedule: /api/my-schedule/:memberId is public (no auth, uses member UUID)
19. Customer auto-linking: on quote submit, findOrCreateCustomer matches by email then phone
20. Activity logging: quote changes auto-logged to quote_activity table with action_type and description
21. Base64 file upload pattern: client reads file → converts to base64 → sends in JSON body → server decodes with Buffer.from(data, 'base64') → uploads to Supabase Storage
22. Finance soft-delete: all finance deletes set deleted_at instead of removing rows (HMRC compliance). All list queries filter by deleted_at IS NULL
23. Finance audit trail: logAudit() records every create/update/delete with before/after JSONB values in finance_audit_log table
24. Follow-up scheduler: node-cron runs hourly, sends 2-step email sequence on day 3 and day 7 for unresponded leads
25. Webhook signature verification: Resend uses HMAC-SHA256 (svix), Twilio uses HMAC-SHA1, both with timing-safe comparison
26. Quote soft-delete: quotes use deleted_at column, excluded from default list queries and CSV exports, restorable via admin
27. Rate limiting: /api/quote limited to 5/hour per IP, /api/chat limited to 30/10min per IP (express-rate-limit)

---

## Implementation Order

Build in this exact order. Each phase depends on the previous ones.

### Phase 1 — Foundation
- Express server with dotenv, CORS, JSON parsing (15MB limit), static file serving from /public
- Supabase client initialisation from env vars
- POST /api/quote endpoint: validate required fields, insert to quotes table, return success
- Deploy to Railway with auto-deploy on push to main

### Phase 2 — Database Schema
- Create quotes table manually in Supabase (core columns)
- Run migration 002 (adds estimation, tracking, workflow, conversion columns + indexes)
- Create jobs, recurring_jobs, team_members tables manually
- Create invoices table manually
- Create quote_activity, chat_conversations tables manually
- Create settings table (key/value store) and pricing_history table

### Phase 3 — Estimation Engine + Lead Scoring
- Build config/pricing.js with default pricing rules for your business type
- Build services/pricingConfig.js (DB override + file fallback + 5-min in-memory cache)
- Build services/estimator.js (calculateEstimate with size detection from form answers + modifiers)
- Build services/scorer.js (calculateLeadScore with qualification status + conversion likelihood)
- Build services/estimationJob.js (async orchestration: estimate → score → update DB)
- Wire into POST /api/quote: after insert, call queueEstimation()

### Phase 4 — Admin Dashboard
- Build middleware/auth.js (bearer token validation from ADMIN_TOKEN env var)
- Build routes/admin.js (quote list with filters, detail, status update, notes, activity log, attachments, CSV export)
- Build pricing settings endpoints (GET/PUT/POST reset/POST test/GET history)
- Build public/admin.html — start with login screen + Quotes tab + Settings tab
- Dark theme, Tailwind CSS via CDN, Poppins font, brand colour

### Phase 5 — Email Automation
- Build services/emailer.js with Resend client
- sendConfirmationEmail (immediate on quote submit)
- sendEstimateEmail (triggered by estimationJob after scoring, includes accept button)
- sendAdminAlert (for hot leads, score >= 80)
- Wire into POST /api/quote (confirmation) and estimationJob (estimate + alert)
- Record timestamps: confirmation_email_sent_at, estimate_email_sent_at

### Phase 6 — WhatsApp Integration
- Build services/whatsapp.js with Twilio client
- Create Twilio content templates (v3 format) for confirmation, estimate, admin alert
- sendConfirmationWhatsApp, sendEstimateWhatsApp, sendAdminAlertWhatsApp
- Wire into POST /api/quote and estimationJob
- Record whatsapp_sent_at timestamp

### Phase 7 — Google Sheets Sync
- Build services/googleSheets.js with Google service account auth
- syncQuoteToSheets (append row on submit, non-blocking)
- updateQuoteInSheets (update row after estimation, acceptance)
- Wire into POST /api/quote and estimationJob

### Phase 8 — AI Chat Widget
- Build services/chatbot.js with Claude Haiku API
- Define capture_lead and prepare_quote_form tools in the tools array
- Build system prompt with business context, service descriptions, pricing, FAQs, behaviour rules
- Build public/chat-widget.js (embeddable IIFE, self-contained, dark theme, session persistence)
- Add POST /api/chat endpoint with rate limiting (30 msgs per 10 min per IP)
- Add GET /api/chat/history endpoint for session restoration
- Add chat_conversations persistence (upsert on each message)
- Add Chats tab to admin dashboard
- Wire lead capture: when capture_lead tool fires, create quote in DB

### Phase 9 — Customer Management
- Run migration 005 (customers table + foreign keys + backfill)
- Build routes/customers.js (CRUD, search, stats, analytics, follow-ups, bulk ops, CSV import)
- Add findOrCreateCustomer() and wire into POST /api/quote
- Add sendFollowUpEmail to emailer.js
- Add Customers tab to admin dashboard

### Phase 10 — Job Scheduling
- Build routes/jobs.js (jobs CRUD, recurring jobs, team members, availability, week view)
- Add sendRescheduleEmail and sendRescheduleWhatsApp to services
- Add Schedule tab + Team tab to admin dashboard
- Add public team schedule endpoint: GET /api/my-schedule/:memberId

### Phase 11 — Invoicing
- Build routes/invoices.js (CRUD, auto-numbering INV-0001, create from job, send email, public view)
- Add sendInvoiceEmail to emailer.js
- Add Invoices tab to admin dashboard
- Add public invoice view: GET /invoice/:token (printable HTML, no auth)
- VAT support: 0%, 5%, 20% configurable per invoice

### Phase 12 — Quote Acceptance
- Run migration 004 (acceptance columns on quotes)
- Build GET /accept-estimate/:quoteId (public HTML acceptance page)
- Build POST /confirm-acceptance/:quoteId (process acceptance, update DB, notify admin)
- Add accept button links to estimate emails and WhatsApp messages

### Phase 13 — Finance & Expense Tracking
- Run migration 006 (expense_categories, expenses, wage_payments, mileage_log, recurring_expenses, income_entries tables + triggers + pre-seeded categories)
- Create Supabase Storage bucket: expense-receipts (public, 10MB max)
- Build routes/finance.js — all 28 functions:
  - Categories: list, create, update
  - Expenses: list, create, update, delete, scan-receipt (Claude Sonnet vision OCR)
  - Wages: list, create, update, delete
  - Mileage: list, create, update, delete
  - Recurring: list, create, update, delete, generate
  - Income: list, create, delete
  - Reports: summary (P&L), cashflow, category-breakdown, tax-summary, export
- Receipt scanner: upload image → base64 → Claude Sonnet extracts date/amount/VAT/supplier → returns items array for category splitting
- Bulk receipt upload: multi-file input, sequential processing, progress bar, review queue, inline editing, "Save All"
- Add Finance tab to admin dashboard (7 sub-tabs: Overview, Expenses, Receipt Scanner, Wages, Mileage, Recurring, Income, Reports)

### Phase 14 — Finance Audit Trail & HMRC Compliance
- Run migration 007 (soft-delete columns on all finance tables, finance_audit_log, capital_assets, tax_savings tables)
- Add logAudit() helper to finance.js — logs all creates, updates, deletes with before/after values
- Add capital assets CRUD endpoints (AIA claims, disposal tracking)
- Add tax savings CRUD endpoints
- Add audit log list endpoint with filters (table, action, date range)
- Add tax forecast and tax report endpoints
- Add Assets, Tax Planning, and Audit Log sub-tabs to Finance section in admin dashboard
- Update all finance delete operations to soft-delete (set deleted_at) instead of hard delete
- Filter all finance list queries by deleted_at IS NULL

### Phase 15 — Automated Follow-Ups
- Run migration 008 (follow_up_step column on quotes)
- Build services/followUpScheduler.js with node-cron (runs hourly)
- 2-step email sequence: Day 3 check-in, Day 7 final follow-up
- Query unresponded estimated quotes, skip accepted/unqualified
- Update follow_up_step and last_contact_at after each send
- Wire into index.js: setSupabaseClient on startup, startScheduler on listen

### Phase 16 — Webhook Validation & Security Hardening
- Run migration 009 (deleted_at on quotes for soft-delete)
- Build routes/webhooks.js with HMAC signature verification for Resend and Twilio
- Log email/WhatsApp delivery events to quote_activity table
- Add rate limiting on /api/quote (5/hour per IP) and /api/chat (30/10min per IP)
- Add input sanitisation (XSS prevention in email templates)
- Add soft-delete for quotes (X button per row, restore capability)
- Add estimation retry for quotes that missed async processing
- Add /health endpoint for monitoring

---

## Important Constraints

- Frontend is separate (Aura-hosted or custom). This repo is backend only.
- Do NOT over-engineer. Keep it modular.
- Do NOT add unnecessary dependencies.
- Keep backend Express-based (Node.js).
- Use Supabase as the database layer.
- British English throughout.
- All prices in GBP (£).
- Use environment variables for all external service config and business identity.
- Static files served from /public.
- Admin dashboard is a single HTML file (public/admin.html) — no React, no build step.
- Chat widget is a single JS file (public/chat-widget.js) — self-contained, no dependencies.
- All admin routes protected by Bearer token auth.
- Never expose Supabase service role key to frontend.
- Never log API keys or customer PII in production.
